reviewText: The book itself is still long winded. Excellent knowledge that takes too long to read and understand.

The producers and presenters did an excellent job in presenting all of the features of the D60 and many useful suggestions on settings and use. The writing and editing are a little rough and one of the presenters feels a need to dress up in a 'big time photographer' suit but the information is all there and presented in a good, easily assimilable form.
